Key Business Insights
💰 1. Revenue Concentration (Very Important 🔥)

👉 A small number of customers contribute a large portion of total revenue.

Insight:

Top customers generate a significant % of total sales
Business is highly dependent on high-value customers

Business Action:

Focus on customer retention & loyalty programs
🌍 2. Geographic Dependency

👉 One or a few countries dominate revenue.

Insight:

Majority of revenue comes from top 1–2 countries
Other markets are underutilized

Business Action:

Expand marketing in low-performing regions
Reduce dependency on single market
📈 3. Seasonal Revenue Trends

👉 Revenue varies across months.

Insight:

Certain months show spikes (likely festive or sale periods)
Some months have low activity

Business Action:

Plan marketing campaigns during low months
Maximize inventory during peak periods
📦 4. Product Performance Imbalance

👉 Few products generate most revenue.

Insight:

Top 10 products contribute a large share of revenue
Many products have very low sales

Business Action:

Promote high-performing products
Remove or rethink low-performing inventory
👤 5. Customer Retention is Critical 🔁

👉 Repeat customers drive revenue.

Insight:

A good % of customers place multiple orders
Repeat customers are more valuable

Business Action:

Focus on retention strategies (email, offers, loyalty programs)
⚠️ 6. Returns Impact Revenue

👉 Returns (negative quantity) reduce overall revenue.

Insight:

Returns lead to revenue loss
Could indicate product quality or delivery issues

Business Action:

Improve product quality
Optimize logistics
📊 7. Business Follows Pareto Principle

👉 ~20% customers/products generate ~80% revenue.

Insight:

Revenue is not evenly distributed

Business Action:

Focus on high-value segments
